<TITLE> Sri Lanka bus blast kills 16, wounds 40:police </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 COLOMBO, April 25 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - At least 16 people were killed and 40 were wounded when a blast ripped through a packed commuter bus during the evening rush-hour in the Sri Lankan capital on Friday, a police spokesman said. "Sixteen people killed and about 40 injured from the explosion," spokesman NK Ilangakoon said
